If you create the following setting in the custom manager page, you could call
every page in your installation with the url parameter mode=test (i.e. https://your.own.domain/?mode=amp ) or with the file extension .amp.html (i.e. https://your.own.domain/index.amp.html ) and the page is shown with the template
chunk  switchTest  and is filtered to valid AMP markup.     Property  Value      Name  Test    Key  amp    Extension  .amp.html    Chunk/Template Name  switchTest    Template Type  Chunk    Cache the Output  Yes    Output Type  AMP    Enabled Resources (Default 'All')  -    Disabled Resources (Default 'None')  -      
